      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BARTIME (7) hasn't made an impression lately despite market confidence. Last start could only manage seventh over 1200m at this track. Rates highly in this lineup and can improve. ROYALZEL (3) settled at the rear then stoked up nicely in the straight to finish fourth over 1200m here last time. Certain to be winding up strongly. BORDER CONTROL (2) settled well back last start and never threatened when 8 lengths from the winner in fifth over 1200m at Marble Bar. Meets some better types this time but a win is not out of the question. STAR POWER (6) built on a nice third two starts back at this track with success over 1200m at Marble Bar eight days ago, getting home by 2.75 lengths. Well placed and there is no reason she cannot score again. GALAXY AFFAIR (1) couldn't bring up the hat-trick last time out but this looks a suitable race. Can bounce back.",
